    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/50.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Calhoun</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 12, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to previous telegrams. Mr. Charles Davis Jameson has been engaged by
                    the Red Cross to study and report upon river conservancy and will leave for
                    Peking via Siberia within a few days. You will be informed of exact date later.
                    You will inform Chinese Government of Mr. Jameson’s appointment and afford him
                    every possible facility in his mission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
